{
    "esm": "0.4.0",
    "metadata": {
        "name": "NOxPhotochemistry",
        "description": "The NOx (NO + NOв‚‚) photochemical cycle that governs tropospheric ozone вЂ” Seinfeld & Pandis (2006) Ch. 6 В§6.2, Eqs. 6.5-6.8, pp. 207-212. During daytime three reactions cycle rapidly between NO, NOв‚‚ and Oв‚ѓ: NOв‚‚ + hОЅ в†’ NO + O (О» < 424 nm), O + Oв‚‚ + M в†’ Oв‚ѓ + M, and NO + Oв‚ѓ в†’ NOв‚‚ + Oв‚‚. In the absence of other oxidants this cycle reaches a photostationary state (the Leighton relationship). Implements four algebraic diagnostic relations: (Eq. 6.5) ground-state O-atom steady-state concentration O = j_NO2В·[NOв‚‚] / (k_O_O2_MВ·[Oв‚‚]В·[M]), (Eq. 6.6) photostationary-state ozone O3_pss = j_NO2В·[NOв‚‚] / (k_NO_O3В·[NO]) вЂ” the Leighton relationship, (Eq. 6.7) the photostationary-state parameter О¦ = j_NO2В·[NOв‚‚] / (k_NO_O3В·[NO]В·[Oв‚ѓ]) which is 1 at exact PSS and deviates when peroxy radicals perturb the cycle, and (Eq. 6.8) the net ozone production rate P_O3 = j_NO2В·[NOв‚‚] в€’ k_NO_O3В·[NO]В·[Oв‚ѓ]. Observed-only algebraic system (no time derivatives): nine variables (five inputs NO/NO2/O3/O2/M encoded as parameters, four outputs O/O3_pss/О¦/P_O3 encoded as state) plus three rate-constant parameters (j_NO2, k_O_O2_M, k_NO_O3). Migrated from GasChem.jl@8c12c048 src/nox_photochemistry.jl:88 (`NOxPhotochemistry` @component). Sibling component PhotostationaryState (src/nox_photochemistry.jl:145) migrates separately to photostationary.esm.",
        "tags": [
            "gaschem",
            "nox-photochemistry",
            "tropospheric-ozone",
            "photostationary-state",
            "leighton-relationship",
            "observed-only",
            "seinfeld-pandis"
        ],
        "created": "2026-05-17T00:00:00Z",
