                {
                    "id": "o3_pss_linear_in_no2_baseline",
                    "description": "Baseline endpoint of the upstream `O3_pss Scales with NO2/NO Ratio` test (test/test_nox_photochemistry.jl:205-228). At NO=1.0e16, NO2=1.0e16 (NO2/NO ratio = 1), the Leighton relationship gives O3_pss = j_NO2В·NO2/(k_NO_O3В·NO) = 4.210526315789474e17 mвЃ»Ві. Pinned at rel=1e-10. Pairs with `o3_pss_linear_in_no2_doubled` to reproduce the upstream ratio assertion O3_pss(NO2=2e16)/O3_pss(NO2=1e16) в‰€ 2.0 (upstream rtol=1e-6): Eq. 6.6 is exactly linear in NO2, so the ratio is exact by IEEE-754 multiplication-by-2 reproducibility once both endpoints are pinned.",
