                    "time_span": {"start": 0.0, "end": 1.0},
                    "assertions": [
                        {"variable": "O3_pss", "time": 0.0, "expected": 8.421052631578948e+17}
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "o3_pss_inverse_in_no",
                    "description": "Complements the upstream NO2/NO-ratio test by exercising the 1/[NO] dependence of Eq. 6.6. With NO doubled to 5.0e16 mвЃ»Ві (NO2 held at the default 5.0e16), O3_pss = j_NO2В·NO2/(k_NO_O3В·NO) = 4.210526315789474e17 mвЃ»Ві вЂ” exactly half the typical-midday default O3_pss of 8.421052631578948e17 (doubling NO halves the photostationary ozone). Pinned at rel=1e-10. This gates the regression where [NO] is accidentally moved out of the Eq. 6.6 denominator.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {"NO": 5.0e16},
                    "time_span": {"start": 0.0, "end": 1.0},
                    "assertions": [
                        {"variable": "O3_pss", "time": 0.0, "expected": 4.210526315789474e+17}
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "o3_pss_independent_of_o3_input",
                    "description": "Structural test: O3_pss (Eq. 6.6) depends only on j_NO2, NO2, k_NO_O3 and NO вЂ” it is independent of the ambient O3 input. With O3 overridden to 5.0e18 mвЃ»Ві (5Г— the default) and all other inputs at their defaults, O3_pss is unchanged at 8.421052631578948e17 mвЃ»Ві (identical to the `typical_midday_all_outputs` value). Pinned at rel=1e-10. This gates the regression where the ambient O3 input is accidentally wired into the Eq. 6.6 expression вЂ” a confusion between the measured O3 and the diagnostic O3_pss.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {"O3": 5.0e18},
                    "time_span": {"start": 0.0, "end": 1.0},
                    "assertions": [
                        {"variable": "O3_pss", "time": 0.0, "expected": 8.421052631578948e+17}
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "o_atom_linear_in_j_no2",
                    "description": "Exercises Eq. 6.5's linear dependence of the O-atom steady state on the photolysis rate. With j_NO2 doubled to 1.6e-2 sвЃ»В№ (all concentrations at their typical-midday defaults), O = j_NO2В·NO2/(k_O_O2_MВ·O2В·M) = 10158730158.730158 mвЃ»Ві вЂ” exactly 2Г— the default O of 5079365079.365079. Pinned at rel=1e-10. Confirms the O atom tracks the instantaneous NOв‚‚ photolysis rate, the basis of the quasi-steady-state assumption underlying Eq. 6.5.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {"j_NO2": 1.6e-2},
                    "time_span": {"start": 0.0, "end": 1.0},
                    "assertions": [
                        {"variable": "O", "time": 0.0, "expected": 10158730158.730158}
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "o_atom_inverse_in_air_density",
                    "description": "Exercises Eq. 6.5's inverse dependence of the O-atom steady state on the total air number density M (the third body in O + Oв‚‚ + M в†’ Oв‚ѓ). With M doubled to 5.0e25 mвЃ»Ві (all other inputs at their typical-midday defaults), the O-atom quenching denominator doubles, so O = 2539682539.6825395 mвЃ»Ві вЂ” exactly half the default O of 5079365079.365079. Pinned at rel=1e-10. Physically this is why the ground-state O atom is more abundant per unit photolysis at high altitude (low M): the recombination sink weakens faster than the source.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {"M": 5.0e25},
                    "time_span": {"start": 0.0, "end": 1.0},
                    "assertions": [
                        {"variable": "O", "time": 0.0, "expected": 2539682539.6825395}
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "polluted_urban_high_nox",
                    "description": "Polluted-urban regime: NO=2.5e17 mвЃ»Ві (~10 ppb), NO2=7.5e17 mвЃ»Ві (~30 ppb), O3=2.5e18 mвЃ»Ві (~100 ppb), O2/M at defaults. Exercises all four outputs at the high-NOx end of the tropospheric range. O3_pss = 1.2631578947368422e18 mвЃ»Ві (~50 ppb вЂ” the photostationary value implied by the NO2/NO = 3 ratio). The ambient O3 of 100 ppb sits well above O3_pss, so О¦ = 0.505 < 1 and P_O3 = -5.875e15 mвЃ»Ві/s < 0 (strong net ozone loss by the pure cycle вЂ” in reality offset by the peroxy-radical production this component omits). O = 7.62e10 mвЃ»Ві. All pinned at rel=1e-10.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {"NO": 2.5e17, "NO2": 7.5e17, "O3": 2.5e18},
                    "time_span": {"start": 0.0, "end": 1.0},
