                        {"variable": "P_O3", "time": 0.0, "expected": -15625000000000.0}
                    ]
                }
            ],
            "examples": [
                {
                    "id": "photostationary_o3_vs_no2_no_ratio",
                    "description": "Photostationary-state ozone O3_pss as a function of the NOв‚‚/NO ratio вЂ” reproduces the GasChem.jl doc-page figure `nox_pss_o3.svg` (docs/src/nox_photochemistry.md, lines 94-135). NO is held fixed at 2.5e16 mвЃ»Ві (~1 ppb) and NO2 is swept from 2.5e15 to 2.5e17 mвЃ»Ві, spanning a NOв‚‚/NO ratio of 0.1 to 10. The Leighton relationship (Eq. 6.6) predicts O3_pss в€ќ [NOв‚‚]/[NO], so the curve is an exact straight line through the origin вЂ” higher NOв‚‚/NO ratios (more polluted conditions) give higher photostationary ozone.",
