                {
                    "id": "phi_vs_measured_o3",
                    "description": "Photostationary-state parameter О¦ as a function of the measured/ambient ozone вЂ” reproduces the GasChem.jl doc-page figure `nox_phi.svg` (docs/src/nox_photochemistry.md, lines 149-183). NO and NO2 are held at 2.5e16 and 5.0e16 mвЃ»Ві (1 and 2 ppb) and the ambient O3 is swept from 5.0e17 to 3.0e18 mвЃ»Ві (~20 to ~120 ppb). О¦ = O3_pss/O3 falls as a 1/O3 hyperbola, crossing О¦ = 1 exactly at the photostationary value O3_pss в‰€ 8.42e17 mвЃ»Ві (~34 ppb). О¦ > 1 to the left (measured O3 below PSS в†’ net ozone production, peroxy radicals active); О¦ < 1 to the right (measured O3 above PSS в†’ net loss).",
                    "parameters": {"NO": 2.5e16, "NO2": 5.0e16, "O2": 5.25e24, "M": 2.5e25},
                    "time_span": {"start": 0.0, "end": 1.0},
                    "parameter_sweep": {
                        "type": "cartesian",
                        "dimensions": [
