                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "o3_pss_heatmap_no_no2",
                    "description": "Photostationary-state ozone O3_pss as a joint function of NO and NOв‚‚ (2-D log-log sweep), surfacing the full Leighton-relationship surface O3_pss = (j_NO2/k_NO_O3)В·([NOв‚‚]/[NO]). NO в€€ [1e15, 1e18] mвЃ»Ві and NO2 в€€ [1e15, 1e18] mвЃ»Ві each span three decades (clean-remote to heavily-polluted). O3_pss is constant along the diagonals of constant NOв‚‚/NO ratio: the top-left corner (high NOв‚‚, low NO) gives the highest photostationary ozone, the bottom-right (low NOв‚‚, high NO) the lowest. The realistic urban band sits near the NOв‚‚/NO в‰€ 1-5 diagonal.",
                    "parameters": {"O3": 1.0e18, "O2": 5.25e24, "M": 2.5e25},
                    "time_span": {"start": 0.0, "end": 1.0},
                    "parameter_sweep": {
                        "type": "cartesian",
                        "dimensions": [
